on a real note tho, my kids are amazing. This year I’ve realized just how resilient kids are. It still blows my mind how awesome these kids are, even when we have to have a come to Jesus moment bc they won’t. stop. talking. 🤣 
••
I love watching their different personalities come together during conversations or activities. I love seeing them power through a difficult assignment and ask for help when they don’t understand something. I love when they show leadership by creating things for the class or helping others when they’re struggling. Being a first year teacher in a pandemic is extremely hard. But being able to love on & learn with these kids in person for the time being makes it sooo worth it. ❤️🥰🥺 
Sorry for the ramble, I’m just so grateful to wake up and teach everyday. ☺️
